Tundra uses a minimalistic approach to programming and requires semicolons 
at the end of statements. Also, field access in records is done using objec
object.field instead of object[field]. The corrected version of your progra
program would look like this:

```tundra
def applyDiscount(price, discount) {
  return price - discount;
}

val raw = {
  price: "20",
  discount: "5"
};

val price = parseNumber(raw.price);
val discount = parseNumber(raw.discount);
val final = applyDiscount(price, discount);
print(final);
```
This program should now give the expected output of `15`.
